Laboratorijų Kainos — a free public website for Lithuania that aggregates blood test prices from all major private laboratory networks (Synlab, Anteja, Affidea, Meliva, Rezus and others) into one place.
Instead of visiting six different lab websites to find the cheapest price for a specific test, users search by test name or browse by category (hormones, vitamins, blood count, etc.) and instantly see a side-by-side price comparison table showing every lab's current price, with the cheapest option highlighted.
Prices are scraped automatically once per day using Firecrawl for page rendering and the Claude API for intelligent data extraction, then stored in a PostgreSQL database. The site is built with Next.js and deployed on Vercel. A lightweight admin panel lets the owner monitor scrape health and review any unmatched test names.
The goal is simple: save people time and money when deciding where to get their blood tests done.